{{Orphan|date=February 2017}}

'''Juliet Sargeant''' is a [[garden designer]].  She was born in [[Tanzania]] but studied [[garden design]] at [[Middlesex University]].  In 2016, her anti-slavery garden was the first show garden by a female black gardener to be exhibited at the [[Chelsea Flower Show]] where it won a gold medal.<ref>{{citation |title=Juliet Sargeant makes history as first black designer at Chelsea Flower Show |author=Tim Stewart |date=16 May 2016 |newspaper=London Evening Standard}}</ref><ref>{{citation |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-kent-36367792 |title=Chelsea Flower Show: 'Modern slavery' garden design wins gold |publisher=BBC News |date=24 May 2016}}</ref>

