'''Kate Crossan''' (also has performed under the name '''Cait agus Sean''', meaning Kate and John) is an [[Ireland|Irish]] singer and composer.
Crossan first gained notice with a band called [[Kitty's Kitchen]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cfmb.icaap.org/content/32.1/BV32.1art26.pdf|title=Kitty's Kitchen|last=Lofthouse|first=Derek|year=1997|work=[[MUSICultures|Canadian Journal for Traditional Music/La Revue de musique folklorique canadienne]]|pages=42–43|accessdate=31 August 2010}}</ref> She now uses arrangements of the acoustic guitar, piano, flute, [[uilleann pipes]], and violin. She released a solo CD Away ... In November 2014 Www.katecrossan.com
